data.text:
When I moved down to London from Scotland, I rented a room in a house in Muswell Hill. So I thought: “This is me, I’m a north London girl now.” In 1987, when I was 31, I decided I had the wherewithal to buy a property, and started to look around locally.

Muswell Hill was upmarket and expensive, so I went to East Finchley instead. When I found this sweet little end-of-terrace house with a narrow but long back garden, I was thrilled.
